---

<GuideLayout
  title="LMS Branding & White-Label Options Compared (2026)"
  description="Custom domains, branded apps, platform branding removal, and white-label reselling — how eight LMS platforms handle brand ownership, and which give you full control."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Guides', href: '/guides' }, { label: 'Branding Compared' }]}
  lastUpdated="2026-03-22"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-navy mb-6">LMS Branding & White-Label Options Compared (2026)</h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
    <strong>Your brand is the reason learners trust you.</strong> When your LMS shows someone else's logo in the URL bar, the browser tab, or the mobile app store, it undermines that trust — sometimes subtly, sometimes not. White-labeling and branding capabilities vary enormously across learning platforms.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaways items={[
    "Most complete white-label for experts: Thinkific and Kajabi both offer custom domains plus branded mobile apps, giving you full visual control on web and mobile.",
    "Best enterprise white-label: Docebo leads with multi-tenant white-labeling, extended enterprise portals, and deep visual customization for multiple brands.",
    "Branded mobile apps are a key differentiator: Thinkific, Kajabi, and LearnWorlds publish fully branded apps under your accounts. Teachable's app lives under Teachable's listing. Podia has no app.",
    "Every serious platform supports custom domains on paid plans — this is table stakes.",
    "True white-label reselling (multi-tenant portals for clients) is only available on Docebo and Absorb. Expert-focused platforms don't support it.",
    "Most limited branding: Podia and TalentLMS offer basic customization but make full white-labeling difficult."
  ]} />

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Custom Domains</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      Every platform in this comparison supports custom domains on paid plans — this is the minimum viable branding requirement. <strong>Thinkific, Kajabi, Teachable, LearnWorlds, Podia, Docebo, Absorb, and TalentLMS</strong> all support full CNAME/DNS setup with automatic SSL provisioning. The differences emerge in how deeply you can customize the experience beyond the URL.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Branded Mobile Apps</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      Mobile apps are where branding matters most — the app name, icon, and store listing directly affect perceived professionalism.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      <strong>Thinkific</strong> offers Branded Mobile — a no-code builder creating fully branded iOS and Android apps published under your developer accounts (Grow+). <strong>Kajabi</strong> offers equivalent branded apps on Growth+. <strong>LearnWorlds</strong> offers branded apps on Learning Center+ ($249/month). All three are genuine white-label apps — learners see your brand, not the platform's.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      <strong>Teachable</strong> has a branded iOS app, but it's published under Teachable's app store listing — learners download "Teachable" and find your school inside. <strong>TalentLMS</strong> similarly uses a generic TalentLMS app. <strong>Podia</strong> has no native mobile app at all — content is mobile-responsive web only. <strong>Docebo</strong> and <strong>Absorb</strong> offer enterprise-grade white-label apps with per-portal branding.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Removing Platform Branding</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      <strong>Kajabi</strong> is cleanest — no "Powered by" badge on any paid plan. <strong>Thinkific</strong> removes it on Growth+. <strong>Teachable</strong> on Pro+. <strong>LearnWorlds</strong> on Pro Trainer+. <strong>Podia</strong> on Shaker ($89/month). <strong>Docebo</strong> and <strong>Absorb</strong> are fully white-label on all plans — enterprise software where white-labeling is expected.
    </p>
  </section>

  <LeadFormModal
    ctaTitle="Need a fully branded learning platform?"
    ctaDescription="Get a recommendation based on your branding requirements — custom domains, branded apps, multi-tenant portals, or complete white-label reselling."
    ctaButtonText="Get My Recommendation"
    variant="inline"
  />

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">White-Label Reselling & Multi-Tenant Support</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      Some organizations need to resell the LMS to their own clients, each with its own branding. <strong>Docebo</strong> excels here — its Extended Enterprise feature creates multiple branded portals from a single instance, each with unique domains, branding, content, and user management. <strong>Absorb LMS</strong> supports similar multi-portal configurations. <strong>TalentLMS</strong> supports branches with per-branch branding, but it's less sophisticated.
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      Expert-focused platforms generally don't support true white-label reselling. <strong>Thinkific Plus</strong> allows multiple sites under one account. <strong>LearnWorlds</strong> has a Network of Schools feature. <strong>Kajabi, Teachable, and Podia</strong> are single-site only.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Platform Comparison Summary</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b-2 border-navy">
            <th class="py-3 px-4 text-navy font-semibold">Feature</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Thinkific</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Kajabi</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Teachable</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">LearnWorlds</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Podia</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Docebo</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">Absorb</th>
            <th class="py-3 px-2 text-navy font-semibold">TalentLMS</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-slate-700">
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 px-4 font-medium">Custom Domain</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 px-4 font-medium">Branded Mobile App</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ Grow+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ Growth+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ $249+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 px-4 font-medium">Remove Platform Badge</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ Growth+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ All</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ Pro+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ Pro+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅ $89+</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 px-4 font-medium">Multi-Tenant Portals</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️ Plus</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b"><td class="py-2 px-4 font-medium">White-Label Reselling</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td><td class="py-2 px-2">❌</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">✅</td><td class="py-2 px-2">⚠️</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">The Bottom Line</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-700 mb-4">
      Branding capabilities should be a non-negotiable factor in your LMS decision. The gap between "custom domain with some color changes" and "fully white-labeled web and mobile experience" is significant. For expert-led businesses, the branded mobile app is increasingly important — Thinkific, Kajabi, and LearnWorlds all deliver genuine white-label apps. For enterprise and B2B scenarios, Docebo's multi-tenant architecture sets the standard.
    </p>
  </section>

  <LeadFormModal
    ctaTitle="Need a fully branded learning platform?"
    ctaDescription="Get a recommendation based on your branding requirements."
    ctaButtonText="Get My Recommendation"
  />

  <FAQ items={[
    { question: "Which LMS offers the best white-label branding?", answer: "For experts, Thinkific and Kajabi both offer custom domains plus branded mobile apps. For enterprise, Docebo leads with multi-tenant white-labeling and Extended Enterprise portals." },
    { question: "Which LMS platforms offer branded mobile apps?", answer: "Thinkific (Grow+), Kajabi (Growth+), LearnWorlds (Learning Center+), Docebo, and Absorb offer fully branded native apps. Teachable's app is under Teachable's listing. Podia and TalentLMS do not offer branded apps." },
    { question: "Can I remove 'Powered by' branding from my LMS?", answer: "Yes, on higher-tier plans. Kajabi removes it on all paid plans. Others require Growth/Pro tier or above. Enterprise platforms have no platform branding by default." },
    { question: "Which LMS supports multi-tenant white-label reselling?", answer: "Docebo's Extended Enterprise is purpose-built for this. Absorb offers similar multi-portal capabilities. Expert-focused platforms generally don't support true white-label reselling." }
  ]} />

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-4">Sources & Further Reading</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-700 space-y-2">
